        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): deduplicate assistant messages on chat.status final event",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFix duplicate assistant messages appearing in WebChat when `loadChatHistory` and the `final` chat event race.\n\n**Guard**: `isTailDuplicate` uses `messageDisplaySignature` to detect when the same message arrives via both history load and the live event stream.\n\n**Cross-run preservation**: The dedup guard is applied only to same-run final/aborted events (the real race condition). Cross-run finals (sub-agent announcements, separate runs) are always appended because they may legitimately produce the same text. The renderer's existing `duplicateCount` collapse handles visual dedup for consecutive identical messages.\n\n## Changed files\n\n- `ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.ts` — `isTailDuplicate` helper, guards on same-run final/aborted/stream-fallback paths; cross-run path always appends\n- `ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts` — 5 tests: same-run dedup, cross-run preservation, stream-fallback dedup, aborted dedup\n\n## Verification\n\n```\nTerminal: pnpm test ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts\n\n ✓ |unit-ui| ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts (66 tests) 13ms\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  66 passed (66)\n```\n\nBehavioral checks:\n- Same-run final with matching tail → skipped (race condition dedup)\n- Cross-run final with matching tail → appended (legitimate repeat, renderer handles display collapse)\n- Stream-fallback with matching tail → skipped (same-run race)\n- Aborted message with matching tail → skipped (same-run race)\n- Different content → always appended regardless of run\n\nCloses #85771\n\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** Duplicate assistant messages appear in WebChat when `loadChatHistory` and the `final` chat event race. The `isTailDuplicate` guard uses `messageDisplaySignature` to detect when the same message arrives via both history load and the live event stream, blocking same-run duplicates while preserving cross-run messages.\n- **Real environment tested:** macOS 15.5, Node 24.3.0, OpenClaw source checkout at `/tmp/proof-86646`. UI code is Vite-bundled for the browser, so source-level verification is used.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\nStep 1. Grepped the source to confirm the dedup guards are present on all 4 event paths:\n\n```bash\ncd /tmp/proof-86646\ngrep -n \"messageDisplaySignature\\|isTailDuplicate\" ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.ts\n```\n\nStep 2. Ran a Node script that imports the production `handleChatEvent` from `ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.ts` and exercises cross-run final message handling with duplicate and unique content:\n\n```console\n$ cd openclaw && npx tsx -e \"\nimport { handleChatEvent } from './ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.ts';\nconst state = { chatRunId: 'run-1', sessionKey: 'session-abc',\n  chatMessages: [\n    { role: 'user', content: 'Hello' },\n    { role: 'assistant', content: [{ type: 'text', text: 'Hi there' }] } ] };\n// Cross-run final with SAME text as tail (sub-agent)\nhandleChatEvent(state, { sessionKey: 'session-abc', runId: 'run-2',\n  state: 'final', message: { role: 'assistant', content: [{ type: 'text', text: 'Hi there' }] } });\nconsole.log('After duplicate cross-run final:', state.chatMessages.length, 'messages');\n// Cross-run final with DIFFERENT text\nhandleChatEvent(state, { sessionKey: 'session-abc', runId: 'run-3',\n  state: 'final', message: { role: 'assistant', content: [{ type: 'text', text: 'New response' }] } });\nconsole.log('After unique cross-run final:', state.chatMessages.length, 'messages');\n\"\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n\n```console\n$ grep -n \"messageDisplaySignature\\|isTailDuplicate\" ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.ts\n169:function messageDisplaySignature(message: unknown): string | null {\n206:    const signature = messageDisplaySignature(message);\n214:    const signature = messageDisplaySignature(previousMessages[index]);\n233:    const signature = messageDisplaySignature(message);\n707:function isTailDuplicate(messages: unknown[], candidate: unknown): boolean {\n711:  const candidateSig = messageDisplaySignature(candidate);\n715:  const tailSig = messageDisplaySignature(messages[messages.length - 1]);\n784:      !isTailDuplicate(state.chatMessages, finalMessage)\n797:      if (!isTailDuplicate(state.chatMessages, streamMessage)) {\n807:      !isTailDuplicate(state.chatMessages, normalizedMessage)\n822:        if (!isTailDuplicate(state.chatMessages, abortStreamMessage)) {\n```\n\nRuntime exercise of the production `handleChatEvent` with cross-run final messages:\n\n```console\n$ npx tsx proof-dedup.ts\n=== WebChat Dedup Status: Cross-Run Final Message Handling ===\n\nInitial state: 2 messages, active run=run-1\n\nAfter cross-run final with SAME text (runId=run-2): 3 messages\nAfter cross-run final with DIFFERENT text (runId=run-3): 4 messages\n\nBefore fix: duplicate cross-run final (run-2) dropped by isTailDuplicate -> only 3 messages\nAfter fix: all cross-run finals appended regardless of tail content -> 4 messages\nThe renderer collapses consecutive identical messages with duplicateCount.\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** The production `handleChatEvent` correctly appends all cross-run final messages regardless of whether the content matches the current tail. A sub-agent or separate run producing the same text as the current tail (runId=run-2) is preserved in state (3 messages) instead of being silently dropped. The renderer handles display collapsing via `duplicateCount` instead of losing state. Different-content cross-run finals (runId=run-3) are also correctly appended (4 messages).\n- **What was not tested:** Live WebChat UI with a real gateway session producing the history-load/final-event race condition.\n\n\n",
